<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-startup-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Startup accounting, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Startup accounting is the work of keeping an early-stage company&rsquo;s books clean, current, and credible from the very first transaction. In practice that means a <code>chart of accounts</code> structured so it still makes sense at Series A as it did at incorporation, every transaction categorized correctly as it lands, a monthly close that actually ties to the bank, and financial statements the founders &mdash; and any lender or investor &mdash; can trust. Done right, you always know two numbers cold: how much cash you have, and how long it lasts.</p>
      <p>What startup accounting <em>can&rsquo;t</em> do is stand in for tax and legal counsel. Equity and cap-table mechanics, R&amp;D tax credits, QSBS eligibility, entity and tax elections, and financial-statement audits are decisions that belong to your CPA and attorney &mdash; and we don&rsquo;t give tax or legal advice. Our job is to make sure the books those decisions rest on are accurate and investor-ready, and to coordinate with your CPA and a fractional CFO so strategy is built on real numbers rather than a spreadsheet nobody trusts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-startup-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Startup accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-startup-need">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
