<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-startup-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who keeps the books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor keeps the books clean and the numbers investor-ready.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The value of startup accounting isn&rsquo;t the software &mdash; it&rsquo;s a steady hand keeping the books clean while founders build the company. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications sets up a chart of accounts that scales, closes the month so it ties to the bank, tracks runway and burn against real balances, and produces statements a lender or investor can rely on &mdash; all against a written scope. When strategy questions come up, we coordinate with a fractional CFO; when tax, equity, or audit questions come up, those go to your CPA and attorney. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and we don&rsquo;t give tax or legal advice.</p>
